        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>57 Queen Anne St | Cavendish Sq<hi rend="superscript">re</hi>.</placeName>
                    <date>Wednesday</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I will take advantage of your most kind offer<ref target="#foot.f2"/> &amp; call on you on Friday about 11 oclock; if I do not hear to contrary I will venture to assume that this will suit you.—</p>
<p>Pray believe me, | Yours very truly obliged | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD was in London between 10 and 14 March 1856 (see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1843.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to W. D. Fox, 15 March [1856]</ref>) staying with his brother, whose address he gives. He attended a council meeting of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4110.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal Society of London</ref> on Thursday, 13 March (Royal Society council minutes).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See letters to J. E. Gray, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1820A.xml" resp="#automat">14 January [1856]</ref>, and to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_453.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Samuel Birch</ref>, 6 February [1856]. Birch translated for CD passages referring to pigeons from an ancient Chinese encyclopaedia and on fowls from ancient Egyptian and Japanese sources. See <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>, 27–8, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7951.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Variation</hi></ref> 1: 205, 230, 247. For a list of CD’s Chinese sources, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6171.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Pan 1984</ref>.</note>
        </div>        
            
